The Divorce Process

The divorce process in Barbados is relatively straightforward. The first step is to file a petition for divorce with the court. The petition must be served on your spouse, and you must wait at least six months before the divorce can be finalized. If you and your spouse are able to reach an agreement on the terms of the divorce, the court will grant the divorce. If you and your spouse are unable to reach an agreement, the court will decide the terms of the divorce.
